emails.subject: RE: Some unclear fields in Corn Dnext SnD dataset
emails.to: Charlie Quaradeghini; Guillaume Goudy; Pablo Figueroa; Support Dnext
emails.body_text:
Hello Charlie 

Regarding the ‘use_floor’ the corn usage for flour is official statistics from Ukraine. 

The volumes are minimal, but it’s for food use. 

Similarly, what is labelled Protein use is what we call ‘use_groat’ in the SND. 

It is also minimum use.

 

Those 2 were data which were officially published by Ukraine before the war.

 

As for the not available rows it’s a technical issue from our side that should be fixed soon but they are also use_groat values

 

If you have any other questions or if you need further clarification please let us know

 

We thank you for your patience and understanding

 

Best regards

Saber Khalfallah

Hello Guillaume/Pablo, 

 

I am looking through the Corn SND dataset (thul-c4ffcc58-c9b0-4935-a0c8-b93f28d7d674) and notice some fields that do not make sense to me, so just hoping you can clarify.

 

I am not clear on what the following items with Item_MappedName ‘Protein Use’, ‘use_flour’ and ‘Not_Available’ (which are all values linked to Ukraine) are representing. Not_Available is a nan Item but does have values. ‘use_flour’ seems like it should be for wheat? ‘Protein_Use’, what does this represent, some aggregation? 

 

Thanks in advance for clarifying!

Charlie
